# Cursor Rules for Tikka Engine Homesite

## Code Style & Documentation
- Keep documentation minimal and focused on business logic
- Prefer self-documenting code over extensive comments
- Only add JSDoc for complex functions or public APIs
- Use descriptive variable/function names instead of comments

## Agent Behavior
- **ALWAYS ask for confirmation before making file changes**
- **ALWAYS ask for confirmation before running terminal commands**
- **ALWAYS ask for confirmation before installing new dependencies**
- Prefer to show proposed changes first, then ask for approval
- When suggesting edits, explain the reasoning briefly

## Project-Specific Guidelines
- Maintain minimalist design aesthetic
- Use existing CSS variables and Tailwind classes
- Follow the established component structure
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Prefer composition over inheritance

## File Organization
- Keep components in `src/components/`
- Use `src/pages/` for page-level components
- Maintain existing naming conventions
- Group related components together

## Styling
- Use the established design system in `src/index.css`
- Leverage existing typography classes (.text-display, .text-body, etc.)
- Use CSS variables for colors and spacing
- Maintain consistent spacing with section-padding and section-spacing classes
- **When adjusting fonts, ALWAYS check the design system first and use predefined typography classes**
- **Avoid ad-hoc font styles at all times**
- **If a needed font style is unavailable, ask to create a new typography class in the design system**
